  <h1 id="service">bad_request</h1>
  <div id="spacer"></div>
  <h2>What is a 400 Bad Request</h2>
  <p>The request is for something bad_request. Authorization will not help.</p>

  <div id="spacer"></div>
  <h3 id="endpoints">Available Methods</h3>
  <p>The following bad_request routes are available:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <span class="label label-primary">GET</span> /bad_request
      <span> - used to get the documentation of this endpoint</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="label label-primary">GET</span> /bad_request/last
      <span> - used to check when the last time a POST was done against bad_request</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="label label-success">POST</span> /bad_request
      <span> - used to send a dummy create request to this endpoint</span>
    </li>
  </ul>


  <div id="spacer"></div>
  <h3><span class="label label-primary">GET</span>  /bad_request</h3>
  <h3 id="Overview">This url will return you the documentation for this end point</h3>
  <div id="spacer"></div>
  <h4>Example GET request</h4>
  <pre>curl -v -X GET 'http://localhost:3000/bad_request' </pre>

  <h4>Response</h4>
  <pre>Status 400 Bad Request</pre>


  <div id="spacer"></div>
  <h3><span class="label label-success">POST</span>  /bad_request</h3>
  <h3 id="Overview">This url will return you a 503 Gateway timeout response code when you try to do a POST request and return some sample json</h3>
  <div id="spacer"></div>
  <h4>Example POST request</h4>
  <pre>curl -v -X POST 'http://localhost:3000/bad_request' -H 'Content-Type: application/vnd.json' -d '{"test": 123}'</pre>

  <h4>Response</h4>
  <pre>Status 400 Bad Request</pre>

  <pre><code>
    '
    {
        "receivedRequest": [
            "request body data"
        ]
    }'
  </code></pre>


  <div id="spacer"></div>
  <h3><span class="label label-primary">GET</span>  /bad_request/last</h3>
  <h3 id="Overview">This url will return you a 200 OK along with the last updated date/time for the latest POST against the endpoint</h3>
  <div id="spacer"></div>
  <h4>Example GET request</h4>
  <pre>curl -v -X GET 'http://localhost:3000/bad_request/last' </pre>

  <h4>Response</h4>
  <pre>Status 200 OK</pre>

  <pre><code>
    '
    {
        "bad_request": [{
            "lastUpdated": "2015-12-10T16:09:48Z"
        }, {
            "mediaTypeUsed": "text/plain",
            "bodyReceived": "username=lalala"
        }]
    }'
  </code></pre>

